nps_comments: I thought this program was really great.  I've been a manager for a while now, and it was so nice to make sure I'm doing the right things.
Thank you; speakers were good and it was nice to expand my network.
The most useful part was meeting other managers.  I liked hearing what they're doing.
Thank you - good session
I've been with Pearson for a long time now, always managing people and this was such a good, practical course.  I learned so much that I wish I would have learned 6 years ago.
I liked meeting other managers - it would have been good to have more time to network and learn from other managers.
I feel like I was put on this program because my manager doesn't think I'm a good people manager.  I knew a lot of this stuff already.
In my previous company, they did manager training and it was poor compared to this.  I liked how there was a mix of administrative advice and soft skills as well.
Thank you
I don't think the course focused on the most difficult parts of being a manager - like having critical conversations around pay and performance.
I didn't think the content covered was applicable.  I've been a manager for many years; I don't think I needed this.

I liked how we did work first on our own time and then met as a group.  I feel like we were able to make the most of our time together, given we had all read the same content/done the same activities.
The facilitators were so knowledgeable and I really liked how practical things were.  I do feel like I can navigate being a manager a bit better now.
I don't think this was particularly useful.
I really liked connecting with other managers.
Speakers were good - I liked how you used experts from around the business.
The operational advice (e.g. logging goals in Fusion) was great - I wish I had that years ago.  I'm not sure how helpful some of the other topics were.
Thank you for inviting me to this; I liked learning about the really practical things I have to do as a manager (like using Fusion).
I loved all of the practical advice given.

I thought this program was going to be better than it actually was.  The sessions weren't interactive and were often quite boring.  I also don't understand how I'll apply most of what I learned to my day to day
I liked the program - I met a lot of really wonderful colleagues across Pearson
I'm not sure this was applicable to my role
A lot of the topics felt irrelevant to my job - nice speakers, though.
Thank you for including me, but I'm not sure how much I gained from this.  I did really enjoy meeting others from different parts of Pearson.
I don't really understand where the topics for the sessions came from.  It would have been nice to learn about stuff that was more relevant in my day to day
It was nice meeting people from across Pearson
The best part of this program was meeting people from around Pearson.  I thought the program itself was okay; the network I've built has been invaluable
The program was nice - I'm glad I got to be involved
I liked being involved in this
I can't see how I would use this in my day to day
The facilitators did a good job keeping people engaged online.  I would have liked more interaction during the sessions, though.
I liked some of the content and it was nice meeting other colleagues from across the business.  Not sure how applicable this was.
Speakers were good and liked meeting people from different parts of Pearson
This program took up a lot of time.  I think it would have been good if it was half the time it actually was - a week was way too much
I loved this program - I thought the speakers were really inspiring.
Thank you for including me
I think this would have really helped me 3 years ago; not sure it's applicable now.
Thank you for running this program - I love it
Loved building my network outside of Pearson - could we do more to build network with fellow Asians within Pearson?
Thank you for a wonderful experience
I wish this program had more visibility across the company - my manager forgot I was even on it
I loved this program
Facilitators were amazing; so inspiring building my network and meeting leaders who look like me
I would have liked to see more Pearson leaders openly promote this program.  Why is it hidden to the rest of the company?
Amazing program - I wish I could have gotten to know the other Pearson participants better
It says a lot that Pearson is running this program - thank you; it makes me know I'm working for the right place
I wish I would have had this program when I was a lower-level manager.  It would have made me realize I could be a leader and perhaps it wouldn't have taken so long for me to get where I am.
